				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree.  This is an excellent post, and should be read by the developers if we can manage it.  
<br />

<br />
One of the things that does make bards so threatening to developers is the fact that we can do SO MANY things.  No other class even comes close to our diversity, IMO, with the possible exception of Beastlords (Tank, Slower, DPS?).  Therefore, we will ALWAYS find ways around the carefully planned roles that SOE will set for us.  They have learned this, and, I daresay, fear us.  Result?  The nerfbat.  Easier to give us nothing then add things later if it's just too harsh, right?
<br />

<br />
This attitude is frustrating, but can also force us to be better, and more inventive players.
<br />

<br />
A few things in our favor over our rivals, the monks, with this expansion:
<br />

<br />
1.  We can selos in most of the new zones.  Also, we get upgrades to calm/mez/snare (though I've lost rolls on all runes that would give me these thus far, and can't truly attest to their utility).
<br />

<br />
2.  Psalm of veeshan, and Dark Echo hold up as extremely useful in Riftseekers.  If a charm lands on the tank, that's it = wipe.  If a bard is in the group, they can be sure that will never happen.
<br />

<br />
The other thing I REALLY like about this expansion, is the newfound availability of GOOD items for single groups.  I'm an officer in a raiding guild, so don't have as much need of out-of-raid upgrades as many do, but respect sony for adding this option for people who don't have the schedule for regular raid attendance.  A friend of mine has been able to get his bard breaking 9k HP buffed with gear earned EXCLUSIVELY outside of raids (Temple of Veeshan quests and LDON gear included on this, but much of it from GoD/OOW).
<br />

<br />
So, let us not lose sight of the good in general that has come with this expansion, nor to forget that our new medley of songs is insipid.</span></td>
