				<td colspan="2"><span>I agree that some kind of “action” on the part of Bards is necessary to prevent future nerfing and repair the damage OoW has caused the class.  The problem is…most of us don’t seem to care!  I’ve talked to several high level bards about the situation; they emote: shrug me.  I know I’m a new to Everquest (I started on Platinum) but the effects of this class wide nerf should be noticeable at any level.  Still, maybe I’m also in a unique position to see the end of Bard’s coming.
<br />

<br />
Think back to the old days, when you didn’t have that ubber powerful Berserker or Wizard to grab your items for you in a pinch.  When you were just starting out in the game, and Bard was your first choice.  What if no one wanted to group with you, knowing you were a nonclass, a weakling until you got the spells needed to sit in the back with the other castors (which is where we’ll be shortly if this trend continues).   
<br />

<br />
Bard’s aren’t going forward.  They aren’t even standing still.  We’re being reduced in quality and effectiveness, from the ground up!  If this trend continues, all of us (higher levels especially) will feel the pinch.
<br />

<br />
