<br />

<br />
To put it simply, they dumbed it down, massively.  The only things that became more effective were direct methods of doing damage to an NPC, healing a PC, and buffing a PC.  Note I said direct methods.  Methods such as pets, charms, preventing damage rather then healing, etc etc were all fairly underbuffed for the expansion.  Being the two classes that relied on these things most dramatically, enchanters and Bards got pretty much left out of the increase in power that supposedly comes hand in hand with an expansion.</span></td>
