<br />
Okay, anybody who's read my posts on this and other boards will know I'm very optomistic.  I generally disagree with bard negativity and I supported the PBAE nerf.  OoW, however, has handed us too much crap for me to see the silver lining.
<br />

<br />
They gave us new DoTs and DD instead of making the old ones scale up.  That's par for the course.
<br />

<br />
But...
<br />

<br />
The lull is a downgrade.  The mez at 67 has half the range and moves the mob, something NONE of us wanted.  The 68 DD focus is such a PoS I won't even hand in a rune for it.  The VoV is of very limited use thanks to the recast time. 
<br />

<br />
In addition the lvl 70 title Performer is stupid and our epic 1.5 quest is INSANE.  The second fight in DN is a 2.0 fight, not a 1.5 fight.
<br />

<br />
I can't find a silver lining this time.  
<br />

<br />
This will be my last expansion.
<br />

<br />
In all my years of playing I've never been so angry at, or disappointed in, the devs.
<br />

<br />
Dlandridel Cadence
<br />
Bard of Grey Hawke 
<br />
Karana Server </span></td>
