				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The lull is a downgrade.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
This is actually a misleading oversimplification.  Yes, I dislike the fact that they have changed the way the new lull works.   You cannot use it to pacify a mob and move past it even for the purposes of scouting and targeting for the next lull and that does limit the functionality of it.  At the same time, it lets you split level 66+ mobs which the previous lull simply cannot do under any circumstances.  It is a serious pain to have to have both lulls - one for sneaking around pre-66 content and the other for splitting 66+ content, but they do different things.  To call it a downgrade is not really accurate.</span></td>
