				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: State of the Bard<a name="66390"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 11 04 3:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote"> The mez at 67 has half the range and moves the mob, something NONE of us wanted.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
I am sorry but I disagree with this one. I am happy the mez actually push. I do agree on the range though. Honestly, think about it once you got 67 and 70 mez, you got 1 mez that work like Morell (ok it probably dont make stuff dance <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-9.gif" border="0" alt="Crying" hspace="2" /> but oh well..) and another one that have some &quot;feature&quot; on it. There is times you want to move the mob without breaking the Mez.
<br />

<br />
About the Lull, I have to agree its a downgrade. My point would be however that it doesnt reduce the aggro/frenzy radius of 65 and under mobs. Imho they should add this so we dont have to switch over SSoQ all the time.
<br />

<br />
Finally, I agree completly with Kelraz. Since GoD our use in raids as been tuned down. I would  to point you out for those that dont remember this thread [link]http://www.eqdiva.com/Forums/ShowPost.aspx?PostID=52281[/link] (whats the code to make this a link ?). What I would like you to notice is mostly Harmonae point of view. The problem that we are crying and seeing now is something that we saw that was coming. 
<br />

<br />
Its a pure fact that no one can deny that our song in OoW are pretty much worthless. In GoD we saw our utilities in raid goes down. We are less and less wanted / needed in raids. Before, you couldnt really think raiding without bards. Now you can do it without them easily. We reached a point where if you have more than 3 bards in a raid, the 4th is much more weakning the raid than anything else. I would have hoped for OoW (since we all see it coming with GoD) that they will add us some more song and utility that would make us not necessarly stronger, but make us keep up our usefulness.
<br />

<br />
Unfortunatly, as much I like the new OoW Zone, I am very disapointed toward what they do to bards. OoW nerfed us by the side. They nerfed us by not giving us any song upgrade. They nerfed us by not giving us any bard abilities that are related to what we do. They nerfed us by making content that swept away our utilities. Forget AE mana in raids, no one cares. Forget AE ressit in raids, everyone maxed without. It just save them buff slot, but you can buy some. our damage output, Even with focus song and being with a bunch of Dot/DD (non-wizard, they got a familiar) our overall dps is far less than most other class dps. Sometimes i think that my advante of mezing over chanter is that I can take hits.. but i came to doubt about bard &gt; chanter mitigation.
<br />

<br />
I would have like to see a mana preserv with our Manasong. I would have love to see new AE resist songs that go over Cap and stack. I would have like to see a heal focus component added. I would have liek to see a focus song that increase DoT lenght. I would have like to see a song that increase crit rate. I would have like a focus song that increase combat effect, acuracy, add some cleave ability. I would have love to see a defensive focus song that increase avoidance, mitigation, absorb damage WITHOUT a stupid timer. Its not like we have everything and there is nothing else we could have.  
<br />

<br />
What is the most amazing is, above all, how they manage to almost completly skip any upgrade of our mains utilities. If we could at least get real song, maybe I could reconsider my view of SoE trying to eradicate us.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
