				<td colspan="2"><span>Quote:
<br />
&quot;As it stands for now, from what my friend &quot;speculated about EQ 2&quot; and bards saying how different they would be from eq1, and how there were literally 2 different types (I have absolutly NO clue if this is true or false so don't quote me).&quot;
<br />

<br />
Sorry, but I have to, since the question begs to BE asked: 2 different types of bards?
<br />

<br />
I hate to sound gloom and doomy again, but, if this is true, and it’s the way I think it is, the writing isn’t on the wall for bards as EQ1 knows it.  It’s already burned in the CDs.
<br />

<br />
Think about it.  There have always been two types of bards.  The melle bard, who stands on the frontline to add tank support in a pinch, and the support bard who adds haste and mana, or whatever support songs are needed for the situation.  Anyone else seeing the connection yet?
<br />

<br />
I’d like to hear some concrete info regarding a 2 standard bard for EQ2.  If anyone knows any testers for beta, holler at them and find out.  If its true, and its what I suspect, then the Devs have found the permanent simple solution to the “all powerful” bards.  They cut them in half.
<br />
